      <!-- SIZING GUIDE -->
      <h2>Sizing Guide</h2>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="label">
          <p>How do I find my ring size?</p>
		</div>
        <hr>
        <div class="content">
          <p>Order an adjustable ring sizer RING SIZER LINK or use one of the options below 
            to find your ring size.</p>
          <p>OPTION 1: MEASURE YOUR RING</p>
          <p>If you have a ring that already fits your finger perfectly, measure the inner 
            diameter (mm) of the ring on a ruler. Use the chart below to find your ring size.</p>
          <p>OPTION 2: MEASURE YOUR FINGER</p>
          <p>Wrap a strip of paper snugly around your finger. Mark the overlap with a pen, then 
            lay the paper flat against a ruler to measure (mm). Use the chart below to find your 
            ring size.</p>
          <p>RING SIZING CHART</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="container">
        <div class="label">
          <p>How do I find my bracelet size?</p>
		</div>
        <hr>
        <div class="content">
          <p>If you have a bracelet that already fits well, you can simply measure it with a 
            ruler to find the right size. Otherwise, use the tips below to find your bracelet size:</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Wrap a flexible tape measure, a piece of string, or a strip of paper around 
              your wrist so it is snug but comfortable.</li>
            <li>If using a tape measure, simply note the measurement. If using a string or 
              strip of paper, mark the point of overlap with a pen then measure the string 
              or paper strip against a ruler. This is your actual wrist size.</li>
            <li>Add 1/2" to your actual wrist size&mdash;this is your bracelet size! If you prefer a 
              tighter fit, you can add 1/4" instead. Or, if you like a loose-fitting bracelet, 
              add 3/4' to 1" to your actual wrist size.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
      
